&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Capacity planning&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="capacity-planning"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#capacity-planning" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Exit heads add parameters and bandwidth, while checkpoints trained with a shared head avoid some duplication. Capacity planning must include the deepest-path batch because hard tokens can cluster. Average exit depth does not guarantee peak memory or latency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Benchmarking without fooling yourself&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="benchmarking-without-fooling-yourself"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#benchmarking-without-fooling-yourself" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stratify by task difficulty and token category.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report quality versus full-depth output, not only a static reference.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stress batches where one sequence repeatedly takes the deepest path.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recalibrate across temperature and model revisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;A production failure to design for&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="a-production-failure-to-design-for"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#a-production-failure-to-design-for" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;A traffic shift introduces many structured JSON outputs. Punctuation exits early with high confidence, but quoted identifiers require deeper context and start failing schema validation. The aggregate accuracy looks stable while operational error rises. Calibrate on product-level validators, not only token accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
